#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:41
msgid "Update"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:44
msgid "Update your local `master` branch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:46
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:582
msgid ""
"$ git checkout master\n"
"$ git pull\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:49
msgid "Optionally push `master` to your fork in GitLab:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:51
msgid "$ git push gitlab master\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:52
msgid ""
"to keep it in sync.  The `git gitlab-push` script used to [Share a Topic]"
"(#share-a-topic) below will also do this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:55
msgid "Create a Topic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:58
msgid ""
"All new work must be committed on topic branches. Name topics like you might "
"name functions: concise but precise. A reader should have a general idea of "
"the feature or fix to be developed given just the branch name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:62
msgid "To start a new topic branch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:64
msgid "$ git fetch origin\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:66
msgid "For new development, start the topic from `origin/master`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:68
msgid "$ git checkout -b my-topic origin/master\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:70
msgid ""
"For release branch fixes, start the topic from `origin/release`, and by "
"convention use a topic name starting in `release-`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:73
msgid "$ git checkout -b release-my-topic origin/release\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:75
msgid ""
"If backporting a change, you may rebase the branch back onto `origin/"
"release`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:78
msgid ""
"$ git checkout -b release-my-topic my-topic\n"
"$ git rebase --onto origin/release origin/master\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:81
msgid ""
"Alternatively, for more targeted or aggregate backports, use the `-x` flag "
"when performing `git cherry-pick` so that a reference to the original commit "
"is added to the commit message:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:85
msgid ""
"$ git checkout -b release-my-topic origin/release\n"
"$ git cherry-pick -x $hash_a $hash_b $hash_c\n"
"$ git cherry-pick -x $hash_d $hash_e $hash_f\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:89
msgid "Edit files and create commits (repeat as needed):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:91
msgid ""
"$ edit file1 file2 file3\n"
"$ git add file1 file2 file3\n"
"$ git commit\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:95
msgid "Caveats:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:96
msgid "To add data follow [these instructions](test.md#add-data)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:97
msgid ""
"If your change modifies third party code, see [Updating Third Party Projects]"
"(thirdparty.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:98
msgid "To deprecate APIs, see [Deprecation Process](deprecation.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:100
msgid "Guidelines for Commit logs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:103
msgid ""
"Remember to *motivate & summarize*. When writing commit logs, make sure that "
"there is enough information there for any developer to read and glean "
"relevant information such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:107
msgid "Is this change important and why?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:108
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:234
msgid "If addressing an issue, which issue(s)?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:109
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:235
msgid "If a new feature, why is it useful and/or necessary?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:110
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:236
msgid "Are there background references or documentation?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:112
msgid ""
"A short description of what the issue being addressed and how will go a long "
"way towards making the log more readable and the software more maintainable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:115
msgid "Style guidelines for commit logs are as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:117
msgid "Separate subject from body with a blank line"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:118
msgid "Limit the subject line to 60 characters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:119
msgid "Capitalize the subject line"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:120
msgid ""
"Use the imperative mood in the subject line e.g. \"Refactor foo\" or \"Fix "
"Issue #12322\", instead of \"Refactoring foo\", or \"Fixing issue #12322\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:122
msgid "Wrap the body at 80 characters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:123
msgid ""
"Use the body to explain `what` and `why` and if applicable a brief `how`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:125
msgid "Share a Topic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:128
msgid ""
"When a topic is ready for review and possible inclusion, share it by pushing "
"to a fork of your repository in GitLab.  Be sure you have registered and "
"signed in for [GitLab Access][] and created your fork by visiting the main "
"[VTK GitLab][] repository page and using the \"Fork\" button in the upper "
"right."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:135
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:489
msgid "Checkout the topic if it is not your current branch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:137
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:491
msgid "$ git checkout my-topic\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:139
msgid "Check what commits will be pushed to your fork in GitLab:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:141
msgid "$ git prepush\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:143
msgid "Push commits in your topic branch to your fork in GitLab:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:145
msgid "$ git gitlab-push\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:147
msgid "Notes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:148
msgid ""
"If you are revising a previously pushed topic and have rewritten the topic "
"history, add `-f` or `--force` to overwrite the destination."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:150
msgid "If the topic adds data see [this note](test.md#push)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:151
msgid ""
"The `gitlab-push` script also pushes the `master` branch to your fork in "
"GitLab to keep it in sync with the upstream `master`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:154
msgid ""
"The output will include a link to the topic branch in your fork in GitLab "
"and a link to a page for creating a Merge Request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:157
msgid "Create a Merge Request"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:160
msgid ""
"(If you already created a merge request for a given topic and have reached "
"this step after revising it, skip to the [next step](#review-a-merge-"
"request).)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:163
msgid ""
"Visit your fork in GitLab, browse to the \"**Merge Requests**\" link on the "
"left, and use the \"**New Merge Request**\" button in the upper right to "
"reach the URL printed at the end of the [previous step](#share-a-topic). It "
"should be of the form:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:168
msgid "https://gitlab.kitware.com/<username>/vtk/-/merge_requests/new\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:170
msgid "Follow these steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:172
msgid ""
"In the \"**Source branch**\" box select the `<username>/vtk` repository and "
"the `my-topic` branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:175
msgid ""
"In the \"**Target branch**\" box select the `vtk/vtk` repository and the "
"`master` branch.  It should be the default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:178
msgid ""
"If your change is a fix for the `release` branch, you should still select "
"the `master` branch as the target because the change needs to end up there "
"too."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:182
msgid ""
"For other `release` branches (e.g., `release-6.3`), merge requests should go "
"directly to the branch (they are not tied with `master` in our workflow)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:186
msgid ""
"Use the \"**Compare branches**\" button to proceed to the next page and fill "
"out the merge request creation form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:189
msgid ""
"In the \"**Title**\" field provide a one-line summary of the entire topic.  "
"This will become the title of the Merge Request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:192
msgid "Example Merge Request Title:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:194
msgid "Wrapping: Add Java 1.x support\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:196
msgid ""
"In the \"**Description**\" field provide a high-level description of the "
"change the topic makes and any relevant information about how to try it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:199
msgid ""
"Use `@username` syntax to draw attention of specific developers. This syntax "
"may be used anywhere outside literal text and code blocks.  Or, wait until "
"the [next step](#review-a-merge-request) and add comments to draw attention "
"of developers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:203
msgid ""
"If your change is a fix for the `release` branch, indicate this so that a "
"maintainer knows it should be merged to `release`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:205
msgid ""
"Optionally use a fenced code block with type `message` to specify text to be "
"included in the generated merge commit message when the topic is [merged]"
"(#merge-a-topic)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:209
msgid "Example Merge Request Description:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:211
msgid ""
"This branch requires Java 1.x which is not generally available yet.\n"
"Get Java 1.x from ... in order to try these changes.\n"
"\n"
"```message\n"
"Add support for Java 1.x to the wrapping infrastructure.\n"
"```\n"
"\n"
"Cc: @user1 @user2\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:220
msgid ""
"The \"**Assign to**\", \"**Milestone**\", and \"**Labels**\" fields may be "
"left blank."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:223
msgid ""
"Use the \"**Submit merge request**\" button to create the merge request and "
"visit its page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:226
msgid "Guidelines for Merge Requests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:229
msgid ""
"Remember to *motivate & summarize*. When creating a merge request, consider "
"the reviewers and future perusers of the software. Provide enough "
"information to motivate the merge request such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:233
msgid "Is this merge request important and why?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:238
msgid ""
"Also provide a summary statement expressing what you did and if there is a "
"choice in implementation or design pattern, the rationale for choosing a "
"certain path. Notable software or data features should be mentioned as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:242
msgid ""
"A well written merge request will motivate your reviewers, and bring them up "
"to speed faster. Future software developers will be able to understand the "
"reasons why something was done, and possibly avoid chasing down dead ends, "
"Although it may take you a little more time to write a good merge request, "
"you'll likely see payback in faster reviews and better understood and "
"maintainable software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:249
msgid "Review a Merge Request"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:252
msgid ""
"Add comments mentioning specific developers using `@username` syntax to draw "
"their attention and have the topic reviewed.  After typing `@` and some "
"text, GitLab will offer completions for developers whose real names or user "
"names match."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:257
msgid ""
"Here is a list of developers usernames and their specific area of expertise. "
"A merge request without a developer tagged has very low chance to be merged "
"in a reasonable timeframe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:261
msgid "@mwestphal: Qt, filters, data Model, widgets, parallel, anything else."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:262
msgid ""
"@charles.gueunet: filters, data model, SMP, events, pipeline, computational "
"geometry, distributed algorithms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:263
msgid "@kmorel: General VTK Expertise, Viskores accelerators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:264
msgid ""
"@will.schroeder: algorithms, computational geometry, filters, SPH, SMP, "
"widgets,  point cloud, spatial locators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:265
msgid "@sebastien.jourdain: web, WebAssembly, Python, Java."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:266
msgid ""
"@sankhesh: volume rendering, Qt, OpenGL, widgets, vtkImageData, DICOM, VR, "
"Raytracing, webgpu, QtQuick, QtQml, OpenXR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:267
msgid "@ben.boeckel: CMake, module system, third-parties."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:268
msgid ""
"@cory.quammen: readers, filters, data modeling, general usage, documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:269
msgid "@seanm: macOS, Cocoa, cppcheck, clang."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:270
msgid "@spiros.tsalikis: filters, SMP, computational geometry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:271
msgid "@louis.gombert: VTKHDF, HyperTreeGrid, Catalyst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:272
msgid "@jaswant.panchumarti: Rendering, WASM, WebGPU, emscripten"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:273
msgid "@dcthomp: CellGrid"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:275
msgid ""
"If you would like to be included in this list, juste create a merge request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:277
msgid "Human Reviews"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:279
msgid ""
"Reviewers may add comments providing feedback or to acknowledge their "
"approval. When a human reviewers suggest a change, please take it into "
"account or discuss your choices with the reviewers until an agreement is "
"reached. At this point, please `resolve` the discussion by clicking on the "
"dedicated button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:285
msgid ""
"When all discussion have been addressed, the reviewers will either do "
"another pass of comment or acknowledge their approval in some form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:288
msgid ""
"Please be swift to address or discuss comments, it will increase the speed "
"at which your changes will be merged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:291
msgid "Comments Formatting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:293
msgid ""
"Comments use [GitLab Flavored Markdown][] for formatting.  See GitLab "
"documentation on [Special GitLab References][] to add links to things like "
"merge requests and commits in other repositories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:300
msgid ""
"Lines of specific forms will be extracted during [merging](#merge-a-topic) "
"and included as trailing lines of the generated merge commit message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:304
msgid ""
"A commit message consists of up to three parts which must be specified in "
"the following order: the [leading line](#leading-line), then [middle lines]"
"(#middle-lines), then [trailing lines](#trailing-lines). Each part is "
"optional, but they must be specified in this order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:309
msgid "Leading Line"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:311
msgid ""
"The *leading* line of a comment may optionally be exactly one of the "
"following votes followed by nothing but whitespace before the end of the "
"line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:315
msgid "`-1` or `:-1:` indicates \"the change is not ready for integration\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:316
msgid ""
"`+1` or `:+1:` indicates \"I like the change\". This adds an `Acked-by:` "
"trailer to the merge commit message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:318
msgid ""
"`+2` indicates \"the change is ready for integration\". This adds a "
"`Reviewed-by:` trailer to the merge commit message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:320
msgid ""
"`+3` indicates \"I have tested the change and verified it works\". This adds "
"a `Tested-by:` trailer to the merge commit message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:323
msgid "Middle Lines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:325
msgid ""
"The middle lines of a comment may be free-form [GitLab Flavored Markdown][]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:327
msgid "Trailing Lines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:329
msgid ""
"Zero or more *trailing* lines in the last section of a comment may each "
"contain exactly one of the following votes followed by nothing but "
"whitespace before the end of the line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:333
msgid "`Rejected-by: me` means \"The change is not ready for integration.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:334
msgid "`Acked-by: me` means \"I like the change but defer to others.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:335
msgid "`Reviewed-by: me` means \"The change is ready for integration.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:336
msgid ""
"`Tested-by: me` means \"I have tested the change and verified it works.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:338
msgid ""
"Each `me` reference may instead be an `@username` reference or a full `Real "
"Name <user@domain>` reference to credit someone else for performing the "
"review.  References to `me` and `@username` will automatically be "
"transformed into a real name and email address according to the user's "
"GitLab account profile."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:344
msgid "Fetching Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:346
msgid ""
"One may fetch the changes associated with a merge request by using the `git "
"fetch` command line shown at the top of the Merge Request page.  It is of "
"the form:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:350
msgid "$ git fetch https://gitlab.kitware.com/$username/vtk.git $branch\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:352
msgid "This updates the local `FETCH_HEAD` to refer to the branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:354
msgid "There are a few options for checking out the changes in a work tree:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:356
msgid "One may checkout the branch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:358
msgid "$ git checkout FETCH_HEAD -b $branch\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:359
msgid "or checkout the commit without creating a local branch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:361
msgid "$ git checkout FETCH_HEAD\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:363
msgid "Or, one may cherry-pick the commits to minimize rebuild time:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:365
msgid "$ git cherry-pick ..FETCH_HEAD\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:367
msgid "Robot Reviews"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:369
msgid ""
"The \"Kitware Robot\" automatically performs basic checks on the commits and "
"adds a comment acknowledging or rejecting the topic.  This will be repeated "
"automatically whenever the topic is pushed to your fork again. A re-check "
"may be explicitly requested by adding a comment with a single [*trailing* "
"line](#trailing-lines):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:375
msgid "Do: check\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:377
msgid ""
"A topic cannot be [merged](#merge-a-topic) until the automatic review "
"succeeds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:380
msgid "Continuous Integration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:382
msgid ""
"VTK uses [GitLab CI](https://gitlab.kitware.com/help/ci/examples/README.md) "
"to test its functionality. CI results are published to CDash and a link is "
"added to the `External` stage of the CI pipeline by `@kwrobot`. Developers "
"and reviewers should start jobs which make sense for the change using the "
"following methods:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:388
msgid "The first thing to check is that CI is enabled in your fork of VTK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:390
msgid ""
"Navigate to your fork (change the username in the URL): (https://gitlab."
"kitware.com/username/vtk/)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:391
msgid ""
"Click on `Settings > General`, then expand \"Visibility, project features, "
"permissions\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:392
msgid ""
"Make sure `Project Visibility` is `Public` and `CI/CD` is enabled for "
"`Everyone With Access`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:393
msgid "Click on `Settings > CI/CD`, then expand `General`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:394
msgid "Make sure `Public Pipelines` is enabled"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:396
msgid ""
"The simplest way to trigger CI on a merge request is by adding a comment "
"with a command among the [trailing lines](#trailing-lines):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:399
msgid "Do: test"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:401
msgid ""
"`@kwrobot` will add an award emoji to the comment to indicate that it was "
"processed and trigger all jobs that are awaiting manual interaction in the "
"merge request's pipelines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:405
msgid "The `Do: test` command accepts the following arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:407
msgid ""
"`--named <regex>` or `-n <regex>`: Trigger jobs matching `<regex>` anywhere "
"in their name. Job names may be seen on the merge request's Pipelines tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:409
msgid ""
"`--stage <stage>` or `-s <stage>`: Only affect jobs in a given stage. Stage "
"names may be seen on the merge request's Pipelines tab. Note that the stage "
"names are determined by what is in the `.gitlab-ci.yml` file and may be "
"capitalized in the web page, so lowercasing the webpage's display name for "
"stages may be required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:414
msgid ""
"`--action <action>` or `-a <action>`: The action to perform on the jobs. "
"Possible actions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:417
msgid "`manual` (the default): Start jobs awaiting manual interaction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:418
msgid ""
"`unsuccessful`: Start or restart jobs which have not completed successfully."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:420
msgid "`failed`: Restart jobs which have completed, but without success."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:421
msgid "`completed`: Restart all completed jobs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:422
msgid ""
"There is a `quick` stage, so unless you are confident the CI will pass, it "
"is preferable to run only that by doing:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:425
msgid "Do: test -s quick"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:427
msgid ""
"It is even possible to start a single job be navigating in the merge "
"request's pipeline and click on individual play button. This is a great way "
"to test quickly run a smoke test or debug CI issues without wasting CI "
"resources."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:431
msgid ""
"If the merge request topic branch is updated by a push, a new manual trigger "
"using one of the above methods is needed to start CI again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:434
msgid ""
"Before the merge, all the jobs, including tidy, must be run and reviewed, "
"see below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:436
msgid ""
"If you have any question about the CI process, do not hesitate to ask a CI "
"maintainer:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:437
msgid "@ben.boeckel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:438
msgid "@mwestphal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:440
msgid "Reading CI Results"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:442
msgid ""
"Reading CI results is a very important part of the merge request process and "
"is the responsibility of the author of the merge request, although reviewers "
"can usually help. There are two locations to read the results, GitLab CI and "
"CDash. Both should be checked and considered clean before merging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:447
msgid ""
"To read GitLab CI result, click on the Pipelines tab then on the last "
"pipeline. It is expected to be fully green. If there is a yellow warning "
"job, please consult CDash. If there is a red failed job, click on it to see "
"the reason for the failure. It should clearly appears at the bottom of the "
"log. Possible failures are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:452
msgid "Timeouts: please rerun the job and report to CI maintainers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:453
msgid ""
"Memory related errors: please rerun the job and report to CI maintainers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:454
msgid ""
"Testing errors: please consult CDash for more information, usually an issue "
"in your code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:455
msgid ""
"Non disclosed error: please consult CDash, usually a build error in your code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:457
msgid ""
"To read CDash results, on the job page, click on the \"cdash-commit\" "
"external job which will open the commit-specific CDash page. Once it is "
"open, make sure to show \"All Build\" on the bottom left of the page. CDash "
"results displays error, warnings, and test failures for all the jobs. It is "
"expected to be green *except* for the \"NoRun\" and \"Test Timings\" "
"categories, which can be ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:462
msgid "Configure warnings: there **must** not be any; to fix before the merge"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:463
msgid "Configure errors: there **must** not be any; to fix before the merge"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:464
msgid ""
"Build warnings: there **must** not be any; to fix before the merge. If "
"unrelated to your code, report to CI maintainers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:465
msgid ""
"Build errors: there **must** not be any; to fix before the merge. If "
"unrelated to your code, rerun the job and report to CI maintainers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:466
msgid ""
"NotRun test : ignore; these tests have self-diagnosed that they are not "
"relevant on the testing machine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:467
msgid ""
"Testing failure: there **should** not be any, ideally, to fix before the "
"merge. If unrelated to your code, check the test history to see if it is a "
"flaky test and report to CI maintainers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:468
msgid ""
"Testing success: if your MR creates or modifies tests, please check that "
"your test are listed there."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:469
msgid ""
"Test timings errors: can be ignored, but if it is all red, you may want to "
"report it to CI maintainers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:471
msgid ""
"To check the history of a failing test, on the test page, click on the "
"\"Summary\" link to see a summary of the test for the day, then click on the "
"date controls on the top of the page to go back in time. If the test fails "
"on other MRs or on master, this is probably a flaky test, currently in the "
"process of being fixed or excluded. A flaky test can be ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:476
msgid ""
"As a reminder, here is our current policy regarding CI results. All the jobs "
"must be run before merging, *including tidy*. Configure warnings and errors "
"are not acceptable to merge and must be fixed. Build warning and errors are "
"not acceptable to merge and must be fixed. Testing failure should be fixed "
"before merging but can be accepted if a flaky test has been clearly "
"identified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:482
msgid "Revise a Topic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:485
msgid ""
"If a topic is approved during GitLab review, skip to the [next step](#merge-"
"a-topic).  Otherwise, revise the topic and push it back to GitLab for "
"another review as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:493
msgid "To revise the `3`rd commit back on the topic:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:495
msgid "$ git rebase -i HEAD~3\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:497
msgid ""
"(Substitute the correct number of commits back, as low as `1`.) Follow Git's "
"interactive instructions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:500
#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:568
msgid "Return to the [above step](#share-a-topic) to share the revised topic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:502
msgid "Merge a Topic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:505
msgid ""
"Once review has concluded that the MR topic is ready for integration (at "
"least one `+2`), authorized developers may add a comment with a single "
"[*trailing* line](#trailing-lines):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:509
msgid "Do: merge\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:511
msgid "in order for your change to be merged into the upstream repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:513
msgid ""
"If your merge request has been already approved by developers but not merged "
"yet, do not hesitate to tag an authorized developer and ask for a merge."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:517
msgid ""
"By convention, do not request a merge if any `-1` or `Rejected-by:` review "
"comments have not been resolved and superseded by at least `+1` or `Acked-by:"
"` review comments from the same user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:521
msgid "The `Do: merge` command accepts the following arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:523
msgid ""
"`-t <topic>`: substitute `<topic>` for the name of the MR topic branch in "
"the constructed merge commit message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:526
msgid ""
"Additionally, `Do: merge` extracts configuration from trailing lines in the "
"MR description (the following have no effect if used in a MR comment "
"instead):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:530
msgid ""
"`Backport: release[:<commit-ish>]`: merge the topic branch into the "
"`release` branch to backport the change.  This is allowed only if the topic "
"branch is based on a commit in `release` already. If only part of the topic "
"branch should be backported, specify it as `:<commit-ish>`.  The `<commit-"
"ish>` may use [git rev-parse](https://git-scm.com/docs/git-rev-parse) syntax "
"to reference commits relative to the topic `HEAD`. See additional [backport "
"instructions](https://gitlab.kitware.com/utils/git-workflow/-/wikis/Backport-"
"topics) for details. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:539
msgid ""
"`Backport: release`  Merge the topic branch head into both `release` and "
"`master`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:541
msgid ""
"`Backport: release:HEAD~1^2`  Merge the topic branch head's parent's second "
"parent commit into  the `release` branch.  Merge the topic branch head to "
"`master`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:545
msgid ""
"`Topic-rename: <topic>`: substitute `<topic>` for the name of the MR topic "
"branch in the constructed merge commit message. It is also used in merge "
"commits constructed by `Do: stage`. The `-t` option to a `Do: merge` command "
"overrides any topic rename set in the MR description."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:551
msgid "Merge Success"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:553
msgid ""
"If the merge succeeds the topic will appear in the upstream repository "
"`master` branch and the Merge Request will be closed automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:556
msgid "Merge Failure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:558
msgid ""
"If the merge fails (likely due to a conflict), a comment will be added "
"describing the failure.  In the case of a conflict, fetch the latest "
"upstream history and rebase on it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:562
msgid ""
"$ git fetch origin\n"
"$ git rebase origin/master\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:565
msgid ""
"(If you are fixing a bug in the latest release then substitute `origin/"
"release` for `origin/master`.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:570
msgid "Delete a Topic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:573
msgid ""
"After a topic has been merged upstream the Merge Request will be closed. Now "
"you may delete your copies of the branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:576
msgid ""
"In the GitLab Merge Request page a \"**Remove Source Branch**\" button will "
"appear.  Use it to delete the `my-topic` branch from your fork in GitLab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:580
msgid "In your work tree checkout and update the `master` branch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:585
msgid "Delete the local topic branch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:587
msgid "$ git branch -d my-topic\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/develop.md:589
msgid ""
"The `branch -d` command works only when the topic branch has been correctly "
"merged.  Use `-D` instead of `-d` to force the deletion of an unmerged topic "
"branch (warning - you could lose commits)."
msgstr ""
